Dear Alan,

thank you for your interest in my work. Following is a list of my
pre- and reprints on FFTs. Most of these can be accessed with
anonymous ftp from thrain.anu.edu.au, directory
pub/Area4_Working_Notes.

I will mail you the required two .ps files. Please tell me if I should
mail you the others too.

Yours sincerely,
Markus Hegland

<LI> M.H., 1992, "<a href="Heg92a/algornew.dvi.Z"> A self-sorting 
    in-place fast {Fourier} transform algorithm suitable for vector 
     and parallel processing</a>", Numerische Mathematik, 68 (4),
pp. 507-547,
     1994, preprint as Mathematics Research Report MRR 012-94, ANU.

<LI> M.H., 1993, "<a href="Heg93a/fftftp.dvi.Z"> On Some Block 
    Algorithms for Fast Fourier Transforms</a>", 
    in Proceedings of the Computational Techniques and
    Applications Conference CTAC93 Canberra, pp. 286-284,
    preprint as CMA report CMA-MR51-93. <p>

<LI> M.H., 1993, "<a href="Heg93d/parcopaper.dvi.Z"> Block Algorithms 
    for FFTs on Vector and Parallel Computers</a>",
    in "Parallel Computing: Trends and Applications", 1994 Elsevier.
    pp. 129-136.
    (Figure is <a href="Heg93d/parco.ps.Z"> here</a>.) <p>

<LI> M.H., 1994, "<a href="Heg92d/tensprod.dvi.Z"> An Implementation 
    of Multiple and Multi-Variate Fourier Transforms on Vector 
    Processors</a>", to appear in SIAM J. Sci. Comp. 1995,
    preprint as CMA report MRR 016-94. ANU. <p>

<LI> M.H., 1994, 
    "<a href="Heg94c/fft_on_vpp.dvi.Z"> Real and Complex Fast Fourier
     Transforms on the Fujitsu VPP 500" </a>
     Area4 Working Note 14, and preprint as CMA report MRR 034-94 and
as 
     Joint DCS/CSL report TR-CS-94-07, ANU. <p>

<LI> M.H. and Wayne Wheeler, 1994, 
    "<a href="HegW94/markus1.dvi.Z"> Linear Bijections and the Fast
     Fourier Transform </a>",
     Mathematics Research Report MRR 064-94, 1994, CMA, ANU. <p>


