Dear GBRPer:

Thank you for your support of Grass-Root Basic Reserach Program by your active
particition. Attached is the comment on your proposal from your reviewer.
Being the review organizer, I would like to explain to you how the review of 
your proposal was carried out. This is not only to show you that your
proposals were carefully reviewed, but also to solicit your input to see
anything you feel inapropriate. Your input is very important in order to 
further improve the process. Please send me your comments.

(1) As suggested by one of the applicants to GBRP, I decided to make the
    review process anonymous. In doing this, I covered up all the names
    and the organization. 

(2) We have 17 proposals this year. Eight of them came from CRC, eight from
    MRC and one from SPC. The diversity of topics was a challenge to me to
    find appropriate reviewers because of my limited aquaintance specially in 
    CRC. Due to the nature of the proposals, 5 out 8 reviewers came from
    MRC and 3 from CRC. These reviewers were recommended by others (lab. 
    directors, department heads, and others). They had to show their
    comfortness in reviewing some spectific proposals.

(3) Each reviewer were asked to review two or three proposals. But, they were
    encouraged to look over other proposals so that some sort of calibration
    could be achieved. For each proposal, the reviewer gave the score for
    the research content and the quality.

(4) The review meeting was held. Each reviewer gave his/her opinion toward
    the assigned proposals. If the reviewer favored the proposal, he/she
    try to convince the rest of the committee. Ocasually, when a reviewer
    disfavor one proposal, he/she was also challenged by others. It was the
    way to rule out the personal preference.

(5) Finally, each reviewer selected 6 favorite proposals. The review organizer
    only have one vote to break the tie if it happened. The proposals recieved
    more votes were selected by GBRP.

(6) After the meeting, the reviewers sent the written comments to the review
    organizer. In this comments, they were asked to provide two suggestions
    to the proposal.

    (i)  Suggest something to improve the proposal
    (ii) The suggested outcome from the work if selected.

    The first suggestion is to provide the authors how to improve their proposal
    so that it will fit the scope of GBRP better.

    The second suggestion is to provide the authors a goal to accomplish
    during the summer if the proposal is selected. You don't need to follow
    this suggestion. 

Sincerely,

Long

--------------------------------Attachment 1------------------------
The proposal entitled "Fast Multi-Dimensional FFTs " 

     is __________  
     is not __X___

selected by 1995 GBRP because the amount of the research content is not clear.

The comment of this project is as follows:

------------------------------------------
Can you suggest something to improve the proposal?

Should this proposal selected, what is the outcome you would like to see?


Proposal indicates that algorithms were developed and implemented on vector
machines, and hints that the algorithms are novel and elegantly conceived.
It proposes re-implementation of the algorithm on HP machines, followed by
implementation on a parallel cluster of machines.

As described, the emphasis of the work appears to be re-implementation on a
HP machine, and the research content and/or contribution was not clear.

It might be inferred that re-implementation on a HP machine
may help the algorithm to run significantly faster than anything else
available, and if so, then research contribution might lie in the general
area of attempting to identifying the factors preventing a sequential machine
running as fast as a more expensive vector machine.

Suggested enhancements to this proposal would be to identify the
potential research questions that might be answered.



